                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Psalter, almost perfectly square. Copied in a fine hand, with the
                            letters arranged in columns. The strophes are marked in groups of 10. In
                            a very nice double-slip mahdar. The midpoint of the Psalms is marked
                            with a marginal text, መንፈቁ፥ it's half. The spiritual meaning of the
                            Hebrew letters in Psalm 118 are only partially written. Another hand has
                            tried to finish them in pencil.The short version of Psalm 151. The
                            fourth biblical canticle is the Prayer of Hana, Mother of Samuel,
                            Prophetess (ነቢይት፡). The Song of Songs appears to be in the common
                            edition. The Praises of Mary begins on Monday.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                            <textLang/>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
